headlines.description: — Once the shot left Darius Garland's hands, the Utah Jazz couldn't do anything but hope it didn't drop.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 35, Jazz hold off Cavaliers 109-108

headlines.description: — Miles Bridges scored 32 points and the Charlotte Hornets, without four players, leaned on their best 3-point shooting game of the season and beat the Atlanta Hawks 130-127 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Short-handed Hornets lean on 3-pointers, top Hawks 130-127

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 31 points, Precious Achiuwa had 10 points and 14 rebounds, and the Toronto Raptors beat the Washington Wizards 102-90 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam scores 31 to help Raptors beat Wizards 102-90

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Eric Gordon and Christian Wood both scored 23 points, and the Houston Rockets beat the New Orleans Pelicans 118-108 on Sunday night for their sixth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gordon, Wood guide Rockets past Pelicans for 6th win in row
